A PhraseEditor object stores a single non-null String called phrase that consists of one or more words separated by exactly one space character. There are no leading or trailing spaces. You will write two methods of the PhraseEditor class.

Class information for this question:
  public class PhraseEditor
  private String phrase
  public PhraseEditor(String phrase)
  public boolean startsWithVowel(String word)
  public int countVowelWords()

parts.prompt:
Write the method startsWithVowel, which returns true if the parameter word begins with a vowel (a, e, i, o, or u, in either lowercase or uppercase) and returns false otherwise. If word has length 0, return false.

  /** Returns true if word's first letter is a vowel. */
  public boolean startsWithVowel(String word)

Write the method countVowelWords, which returns the number of words in phrase that begin with a vowel. Words in phrase are separated by single spaces. Your method must split phrase into individual words using indexOf and substring (not split), and must call startsWithVowel from part (a) to test each word.

For example, if phrase is "I am an engineer", countVowelWords returns 4. If phrase is "hello world", it returns 0.

  /** Returns the number of space-separated words in phrase that begin with a vowel. */
  public int countVowelWords()

frq_section.reference_solution:
public class PhraseEditor {
    private String phrase;

    public PhraseEditor(String phrase) {
        this.phrase = phrase;
    }

    public boolean startsWithVowel(String word) {
        if (word.length() == 0) {
            return false;
        }
        String first = word.substring(0, 1);
        return first.equals("a") || first.equals("e") || first.equals("i")
            || first.equals("o") || first.equals("u")
            || first.equals("A") || first.equals("E") || first.equals("I")
            || first.equals("O") || first.equals("U");
    }

    public int countVowelWords() {
        int count = 0;
        String remaining = phrase;
        while (remaining.length() > 0) {
            int space = remaining.indexOf(" ");
            String word;
            if (space == -1) {
                word = remaining;
                remaining = "";
            } else {
                word = remaining.substring(0, space);
                remaining = remaining.substring(space + 1);
            }
            if (startsWithVowel(word)) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}

